---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-iran', text: 'Leaving Iranian Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'sanctions-considerations', text: 'Sanctions Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Canadian Expat Insurance', href: '/best/canadian-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'usNetwork', header: 'US Network' },
  { key: 'euNetwork', header: 'EU Network' },
  { key: 'iranCoverage', header: 'Iran Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', usNetwork: 'Strong', euNetwork: 'Excellent', iranCoverage: 'Excluded*', price: '$175/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', usNetwork: 'Good', euNetwork: 'Excellent', iranCoverage: 'Excluded*', price: '$165/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', usNetwork: 'Excellent', euNetwork: 'Excellent', iranCoverage: 'Excluded*', price: '$190/mo' },
  { provider: 'April International', usNetwork: 'Good', euNetwork: 'Strong', iranCoverage: 'Excluded*', price: '$155/mo' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', usNetwork: 'Excellent', euNetwork: 'Good', iranCoverage: 'Excluded', price: '$170/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Iranian Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Iranian expats. Find coverage for the US, Canada, Europe, and other destinations with guidance on sanctions-related limitations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Iranian Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Iranian nationals abroad face unique insurance challenges. Here's how to find coverage in the US, Canada, Europe, and beyond."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/iranian-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Iranian expats are found worldwide—in the US (especially California), Canada (Toronto, Vancouver), Germany, UK, and beyond. Insurance challenges exist due to sanctions, but coverage is available. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Iranian expats. Strong US and EU networks, available to Iranian nationals.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Excellent European coverage. Available to Iranians with proper residence documentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks.</li>
    <li><strong>April International:</strong> French insurer with competitive pricing. Good European option.</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Strong US networks. Good for US-based Iranians.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Important: Iran Coverage Excluded"
    description="Due to international sanctions, most insurers exclude Iran from coverage. Travel to Iran is typically not covered. Plan healthcare for Iran visits separately."
    buttonText="Get Available Coverage"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-iran">Leaving Iranian Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Iran has a mixed healthcare system. Here's what you're leaving:
  </p>

  <h3>Iranian Social Security</h3>
  <p>
    The Iranian social security system (Tamin Ejtemaei) provides healthcare to contributing workers. Coverage is limited to Iran—there's no international coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Iranian Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private insurers in Iran (Iran Insurance, Asia Insurance) provide domestic coverage. These don't extend internationally and face transaction challenges due to sanctions.
  </p>

  <h3>Healthcare Quality in Iran</h3>
  <p>
    Iran has developed medical facilities, particularly in Tehran. However, sanctions have affected medical supplies and equipment availability. Many Iranians seek treatment abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Medical Tourism Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Some Iranian expats return to Iran for affordable medical procedures. This requires separate planning—international insurance typically won't cover Iran.
  </p>

  <h2 id="sanctions-considerations">Sanctions Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    International sanctions affect insurance options for Iranians:
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage Availability</h3>
  <p>
    Most major international insurers can cover Iranian nationals living abroad. The key factor is your residence country—not your nationality. Iranian residents abroad can typically obtain coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Iran Exclusion</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage for treatment in Iran is typically excluded due to sanctions compliance. Travel to Iran is usually excluded. Emergency treatment during Iran visits is typically not covered.
  </p>

  <h3>Payment Considerations</h3>
  <p>
    Iranian banking restrictions may complicate premium payments. Most Iranian expats pay from non-Iranian bank accounts. International credit cards and wire transfers from your host country work.
  </p>

  <h3>Documentation Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    Insurers may require additional documentation proving your residence abroad. This is standard compliance procedure. Provide passport, residence permit, and local address documentation.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">US-Based Iranians</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Iranian-Americans and Iranian residents in the US face additional considerations due to US sanctions. However, US-based insurers do provide coverage. Ensure you work with insurers experienced with Iranian clients.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-4">*Iran coverage excluded due to international sanctions.</p>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage available to Iranian nationals. Strong US networks important for the large Iranian-American community. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    Iran is excluded from coverage. Good option for established Iranian expats with stable residence abroad.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Iranian expats wanting reliable global coverage with strong US networks.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers excellent European coverage available to Iranian nationals with proper documentation. Strong networks throughout the EU—particularly valuable for Iranians in Germany.
  </p>

  <p>
    Iran excluded. Good European option at competitive pricing.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Iranian expats in EU countries seeking strong European networks.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Available to Iranian nationals with residence abroad. Top-tier service quality.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Iranian professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>April International</h3>
  <p>
    April International is a French insurer with good EU coverage at competitive prices. Available to Iranians with European residence. Good for Western Europe.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Iranian expats in Europe seeking affordable comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>GeoBlue</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue offers strong US coverage with excellent domestic networks. Good option for Iranian-Americans and US residents. US focus with international travel benefits.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Iranian expats in the US who prioritize strong US networks.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Coverage Is Available"
    description="Despite sanctions, Iranian nationals living abroad can obtain international health insurance. The key is your residence status, not just your nationality."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Iranian diaspora concentrates in specific countries:
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Iranian diaspora, concentrated in California (especially Los Angeles). "Tehrangeles" has significant Persian community, Persian-speaking doctors, and familiar services. US healthcare is expensive—comprehensive coverage essential.
  </p>

  <h3>Canada</h3>
  <p>
    Large Iranian community in Toronto and Vancouver. Provincial healthcare covers residents after waiting periods. International insurance covers the gap and provides enhanced access.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Iranian community. German statutory insurance (GKV) covers employed residents. International insurance available for those outside the German system.
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Iranian community in London and other cities. NHS covers legal residents. Private insurance supplements NHS access.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can Iranians get international insurance?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes. Iranian nationals living abroad can obtain international health insurance. Your residence status matters—insurers cover you based on where you live, not just your nationality.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Iran covered?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">No. Due to sanctions, most international insurers exclude Iran from coverage. Travel to Iran and healthcare in Iran are typically not covered.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">How do I pay premiums?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Pay from non-Iranian bank accounts. International credit cards and wire transfers from your host country bank work. Iranian bank accounts may face transaction restrictions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What documentation is needed?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Insurers may request proof of residence abroad—passport, residence permit, local address. This is standard compliance procedure. Be prepared to provide documentation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about visiting Iran?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Plan healthcare for Iran visits separately. Your international insurance won't cover you there. Consider travel insurance that might cover Iran, or plan for out-of-pocket expenses.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Are there Persian-speaking services?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Few international insurers offer Farsi support. However, areas with large Iranian communities (Los Angeles, Toronto) have Persian-speaking healthcare providers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Iranian nationals abroad can obtain international health insurance. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> offers reliable coverage with strong US networks—critical for the large Iranian-American community. <strong>Allianz Care</strong> provides excellent European coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium worldwide coverage. <strong>GeoBlue</strong> suits US-focused needs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Accept that Iran coverage is excluded due to sanctions. Plan healthcare for Iran visits separately. Focus on comprehensive coverage for your actual residence country.
  </p>

</PageShell>
